Evan amassed 750 carries for 6,384 yards (8.5-yard average) and 90 touchdowns during his high school career in metropolitan Washington D.C., at the same time starring as an elite-level lacrosse player (was recruited by Johns Hopkins and Virginia, among others). Redshirted in 2006. Was the No. 2 back in '07 when he played in 11 games and rushed 82-513-5 (6.3) with three receptions for 18 yards (6.0) and zero TDs. Suffered a thigh bruise against Iowa and sustained a sprained right ankle against Temple that limited him to 12 carries in the last three games. In '08, established a PSU sophomore rushing record by starting 12-of-13 games (gave way to four-receiver set against Ohio State) and piling up 191-1,236-12 (6.5) on the ground with 17-155-0 (9.1) receiving. Sprained his left knee in the Rose Bowl against USC. Started all 13 games in '09, toting 205-1,169-6 (5.7) with 16-187-2 (11.7) receiving and six punt returns for eight yards (1.3). Started all 13 games in '10 and became Penn State's all-time leading rusher after posting 208-1,014-6 (4.9) rushing with 25-202-1 (8.1) receiving. Graduated.
